The Shadowknight's eyes were wide open with terror. He was held down. His body unmoving. His mind unraveling. His sanity fleeing. A large skeleton was on top of him. Sitting on him. Holding down both his strong arms by the wrist, with one skeletal hand. The other hand quickly ripped off the Shadowknight's armor, throwing the pieces to the side. Each piece of metal that fell, seemed to ring in the Shadowknight's ears and would not stop. The huge skull of the undead creature, loomed over his face. Sniffing at the blood leaking out of the man's mouth.<br>
&quot;Get rid of the outer shell, hmm?&quot; The large skeleton said in a cruel booming voice. &quot;Get RID of it! Get to the tasty parts.&quot; The skeleton ran the sharp tip of it's finger down the Shadowknight's chest, cutting to the bone. The skeleton brought it's bloody fingertip up to it's &quot;face&quot;, looking at it with a tilt of it's head. &quot;The blood of the &quot;Chosen Ones&quot;. How I looked for it for soooo long.&quot; The skeleton put it's finger in between it's teeth, as a person would, if they were licking their finger. There were no lips or tongue on the skeleton, yet the fingertip came away clean. &quot;It is time to eat. Feel free to scream.&quot; the skeleton said in a most casual manner. The Shadowknight tried to hold his concentration enough to send a mental message to another &quot;Chosen One&quot;, whom he knew. Then all the Shadowknight could do was scream, as the large skeleton opened it's jaw bones wide, then clamped down on the man's chest. Then slowly brought it's teeth together, ripping flesh and muscle and began to chew.<br>
<br>
A young, confident woman who served Innoruuk as a Shadowknight, was herself a &quot;Chosen One&quot;. She and the Shadowknight currently being tortured, were &quot;lovers&quot; from time to time. She heard his &quot;call&quot; in her mind, then heard his scream. Her ears started to bleed.<br>
 She ran down the long tunnels of the underworld of Freeport and found one of her superiors. She explained what little she was aware of, then ran off to find her &quot;lover&quot;. All she knew, was that he was in an abandoned hut somewhere in the Eastern Commonlands.<br>
<br>
Daon placed the large box on top of the Steel Warrior's crotch. It was a crate, well made, with very little room for anything to fall out of between the boards. Small, hairy, black and brown legs seemed to dart in and out of the spaces between boards. Occasionally a thin, hairless leg would &quot;peek&quot; out as well. Almost as if testing the air. The sound of small things scratching and scuttling about came from inside. Daon then took his time, walking to the other side of the table. Stood near the group of weapons the Warrior had used. Daon wanted him to look his way eventually, and see the weapons so easily in view and too far to reach. Daon stood there patiently. The hood covering his features completely. Not his eyes, his nose, nor even his chin could be seen. Daon stood with his hands together, the sleeves of the red robe covering his gloves.<br>
&quot;I am not afraid of you!&quot; The warrior growled, breathing heavily in defiance. Daon undid the leather strap holding the Warrior's head in place. &quot;I do not NEED for you to fear me.&quot; the Necromancer calmly said. &quot;I only wish for you to suffer.&quot; Then Daon held up the vial of acid over the Warrior's head.<br>
<br>
The woman Shadowknight of the Dismal Rage, ran hard throughout the Commonlands. She never paid attention to what other buildings existed, besides the ones she sold to when hunting. Now she wracked her mind to try and remember which one was abandoned. She stopped for a moment, exhausted. Her hands on her knees, gasping for breath. &quot;That bastard better not be with another woman!&quot; she gasped out loud. &quot;If it's just one of his sluts who decided to rob him while his pants were down..I'll kill him!&quot; She looked around and saw, off in the distance, a building she could not remember being occupied or not. Drawing her bastard sword, she half walked, half stumbled from exhaustion, towards the hut. She did not even think of knocking. She was a Shadowknight. She would kick down the door. If she was wrong... well, she did not know what to do then. She was all out of ideas. Stopping at the doorway, long enough to inhale deeply, she brought her foot up and crashed it into the door. The door did not move. She swore an unholy oath to Innoruuk, then screamed as the door swung open and a large skeletal hand shot out. The two middle fingers piercing through her eyes and hooking down, to hold her by the skull and drag her in.  Her nails clawed at the door frame for brief seconds, before disappearing into the hut. The door slammed shut.<br>
