 Someone once said &quot; When you write, don't hold back. Let it all flow out even if it disturbs you while writing it. Sometimes in our stories, the monsters, villains, or horrible scenes, is actually our subconscious trying to remind us and our readers of the real issues or real life monsters that are out there. it's easy to forget and turn the other cheek, when we are safe in our homes or with our friends and loved ones. Disturbing material, is sometimes &quot;just&quot; necessary to help the reader understand a character or monster. Sometimes it's to make us wake up and remember we are not in The Magic Kingdom. Writing has many levels to it. You won't always know until AFTER.&quot; <br>
